                            "text": "393 AC - See through the eyes of someone else and try to understand. That's what you told me to do. I remember you set me on your lap when I came home from school and asked me what was wrong. I said that it was Hossam again, that he had pushed me and pulled my hair. And as usual, I had reacted badly and flipped out, so that the teacher had asked for a meeting with my parents to sort it all out. You asked me what he had done and you said that maybe he just wanted to get my attention. I followed your advice and tried to understand, and I saw that you were right. A few days later, we were inseparable…\r\n\r\nI close my eyes and open my mind to Halua. I'm with him, in him, as he flies over the Thessalian Quadrant. I still feel his distress, while he feels my presence. Little by little, his memories come to me. And mine rise to the surface of his mind, like bubbles that then burst and release impressions, vague recollections that become clearer as the days go by. He had lived and grown among humans. He was initially treated kindly, almost with reverence, before being chased away when he became a burden. He was a protector, and he'd been stripped of his purpose, his job, his role. I was now seeing through his eyes, and I was starting to understand…\r"
                        },
